This paper deals with combinatorial auctions, which are a classic topic in computer science and economics. The use of submodular valuations is also a well-studied area in computer science, particularly in the context of optimization and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and economics. The paper also deals with approximation algorithms, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science, suggesting categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of submodular functions also suggests categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
